    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Port messages are used primarily by the distributed objects system. You should implement inter-application communication using distributed objects whenever possible and use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsportmessage"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " only when necessary."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsportmessage"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object has three major parts: the send and receive ports, which are "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsport"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects that link the sender of the message to the receiver, and the components, which form the body of the message. The components are held as an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsarray"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object containing "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsdata"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsport"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects. The "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsportmessage/1407464-sendbeforedate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " message sends the components out through the send port; any replies to the message arrive on the receive port. See the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsport"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class specification for information on handling incoming messages."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsportmessage"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instance can be initialized with a pair of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsport"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects and an array of components. A port message's body can contain only "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsport"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsdata"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects. In the distributed objects system the byte/character arrays are usually encoded "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsinvocation"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects that are being forwarded from a proxy to the corresponding real object."
